		h1.page-header Installation Readme

		p Welcome to the installation application of the Atomia Platform. Before we get started there are a couple of decisions that need to be made on your part. This installation is done in a step-by-step process, please follow it in sequence to ensure that your environment is setup according to best current practices.

		legend Requirements
		p The first step in doing a successful installation of Atomia is already done, you have installed this installation application :) Good job!. The next steps are not quite as easy, but necessary nonetheless.

		legend Servers
		p Naturally you will need a couple of servers where we can deploy the services needed to make the Atomia Platform work. This guide assumes that you are installing a full scale production environment which isolates most services on separate servers. You can, of course, choose if you provision the machines described below before you start or do it as you go. The following basic requirements need to be in place for each server you provision:

		ul
			li Basic installation of required Operating System
			li Server should be able to connect to Puppetmaster (and the installation service if these are on different servers)
			li Server should be able to connect to the internet
			li The server hostname should be resolvable

